  "prompt": "How do you buy a car at an auctions?",
  "response": "Buying a car at an auction involves several steps:\n\n1. Research\n- Find reputable auto auctions (government, dealer, salvage)\n- Decide between in-person or online auctions\n- Understand auction types (public, dealer-only)\n\n2. Pre-Auction Preparation\n- Set a budget\n- Check auction listings\n- Get vehicle history reports\n- Inspect vehicle details and condition\n- Determine maximum bid price\n\n3. Registration\n- Register with the auction house\n- Provide necessary identification\n- Pay potential registration/deposit fees\n- Get auction bidding credentials\n\n4. Vehicle Inspection\n- Attend preview/inspection days\n- Thoroughly examine vehicles\n- Check for damage, mechanical issues\n- Have a mechanic inspect if possible\n\n5. Bidding Process\n- Understand auction rules\n- Know your maximum bid\n- Be prepared for competitive bidding\n- Stay calm and disciplined\n- Watch for additional fees\n\n6. After Winning\n- Pay full amount immediately\n- Complete required paperwork\n- Arrange vehicle transportation\n- Get necessary registration/title transfer\n\n7. Additional Considerations\n- Most auctions are \"as-is\"\n- No warranties typically included\n- Understand return/refund policies\n- Factor in potential repair costs\n\nCareful preparation is key to successful auction car buying.",
